LARDD 1
TITLE LardOS Releases
TEXT Every feature addition gets a release entry. The running kernel version is the active release.
TEXT Suffix policy: a=official, b=beta-experimental, p=hotpatch.
TEXT Hardware profiles extend releases by target: universal, seabios, ami, vbox, usb, realpc.
TEXT New or risky feature bundles should use b first; a is for promoted stable builds only.

SECTION v1.52.5p
ITEM Hotpatch for scrollbar visibility after v1.52.4p.
ITEM The response pane now always draws a recognizable scrollbar: outer frame, top and bottom arrow caps, track, and thumb.
ITEM No-overflow output still shows a full disabled thumb so users can see that the scrollbar exists even when there is nothing to scroll.
ITEM Scrollable output continues to use a proportional thumb and the drag hit-test now matches the visible track between the arrow caps.
ITEM Keeps the cursor edge hotpatch and user-owned Unicode cursor path intact.
ITEM Build, ISO structure checks, and QEMU GUI smoke tests were rerun for hotpatch readiness.

SECTION v1.52.4p
ITEM Hotpatch for the remaining edge GUI issues reported after v1.52.3p.
ITEM Lets the Unicode cursor hotspot reach the bottom and right edge while the cursor art clips past the screen like a normal desktop pointer.
ITEM Moves screenram flushing before cursor drawing so screenram corner storage cannot hide the mouse cursor.
ITEM Makes disabled/no-overflow scrollbars visible with a muted rail and grip instead of disappearing into the output pane.
ITEM Refines the default U+E004 mouse glyph with a bright tip so it remains visible at the screen edge while staying user-owned and editable.
ITEM Build, ISO structure checks, and QEMU GUI smoke tests were rerun for hotpatch readiness.

SECTION v1.52.3p
ITEM Hotpatch for the remaining GUI boxed areas reported after v1.52.2p.
ITEM Aligns the GUI overlay output frame with the real response view so the accent line no longer crosses the input field.
ITEM Renders the Unicode cursor without hover-border effects, scales it larger for pointer readability, and seeds the default U+E004 mouse glyph as a stable non-live cursor.
ITEM Hides the bright scrollbar thumb when there is no scrollable overflow and keeps a quiet rail, while preserving proportional thumbs for longer output.
ITEM Keeps the user-owned cursor and picture Unicode editing path intact.
ITEM Build, ISO structure checks, and QEMU GUI smoke tests were rerun for hotpatch readiness.

SECTION v1.52.2p
ITEM Hotpatch for GUI mouse and response-scroll regressions after the v1.52.1p polish release.
ITEM Keeps the user-owned U+E004 cursor picture path but removes the doubled cursor draw so the glyph appears as one clean pointer.
ITEM Enables PS/2 IntelliMouse 4-byte packets and routes the wheel into response/output pane scrolling.
ITEM Uses one shared response-view rectangle for rendering, focus, wheel, and scrollbar hit-testing so visible controls and mouse behavior line up.
ITEM Computes scrollbar thumb length and position from visible rows versus total response lines, matching the actual scroll ratio.
ITEM Build, ISO structure checks, and QEMU screen smoke tests were rerun for hotpatch readiness.

SECTION v1.52.1p
ITEM Hotpatch for two small GUI polish regressions after the v1.52.0a official release.
ITEM Replaces the default U+E004 mouse Unicode picture with a clearer pointer-shaped cursor while keeping the slot user-owned and editable.
ITEM Moves the response/output pane below the input box using input-relative layout so URL/Cmd text, Response/LSH labels, and output lines no longer overlap.
ITEM Keeps the values/user-law official release direction unchanged and does not remove any existing feature surface.
ITEM Build, ISO structure checks, and QEMU screen smoke tests were rerun for hotpatch readiness.

SECTION v1.52.0a
ITEM Official promotion of the LardOS user-law value statement refresh without feature loss.
ITEM Keeps values and philosophy as direct shell aliases for rendering userlaw.lardd from inside LardOS.
ITEM Keeps the expanded userlaw reset text covering user ownership, visibility, local self-reliance, explainable automation, reversibility, repair over halt, user-grantable power, native formats, honest releases, and visible OSLink communication.
ITEM Keeps the control room and control command pointing users toward the values document as a first-class control surface.
ITEM Release media uses official a-channel versioning with universal, seabios, ami, vbox, usb, and realpc IMG/ISO artifacts.

SECTION v1.52.0b
ITEM Refreshes the LardOS user-law value statement so the OS restates its user-owned, visible, editable, explainable, recoverable design goals.
ITEM Adds values and philosophy shell aliases that render userlaw.lardd directly from inside LardOS.
ITEM Expands userlaw.lardd and userlaw reset with principles for local self-reliance, explainable automation, reversibility, repair over halt, honest releases, native formats, and visible OSLink communication.
ITEM The control room and control command now point users toward the values document as a first-class control surface.
ITEM This ships as beta because the value statement is a visible policy surface that should settle before official promotion.

SECTION v1.51.0b
ITEM Makes the default GUI cursor a pretty mouse picture glyph instead of a plain arrow fallback.
ITEM The mouse cursor lives in the user-owned picture Unicode range at U+E004 and is named mouse in glyphmap.lardd.
ITEM cursor mouse and cursor default restore the U+E004 mouse glyph, while cursor set U+E000 still lets the user choose another editable slot.
ITEM glyph demo now seeds U+E004 with the same mouse picture, and glyph pixel/rename/move/copy can edit it like any other user-owned Unicode picture.
ITEM Transparent pixels now stay transparent during live image-glyph rendering so shaped cursor glyphs do not grow a solid box.
ITEM This ships as beta while the new default cursor art and hardware-profile media are tested across targets.

SECTION v1.50.0b
ITEM Adds hardware release profiles as a separate axis from the a/b/p stability suffix.
ITEM RELEASE_HW=universal, seabios, ami, vbox, usb, or realpc now changes release directory, artifact names, ISO volume label, and embedded hardware profile.
ITEM make release-all-hardware builds the whole hardware profile set with IMG and ISO media for each target.
ITEM release policy, ver, and status now show the selected hardware profile inside LardOS.
ITEM This ships as beta because hardware-specific release packaging should be tested across real machines and virtual machines before promotion.

SECTION v1.49.1p
ITEM Hotpatch for real-machine and VM boot reliability after the v1.49.0a official release.
ITEM Added a hybrid ISO MBR path so the ISO can boot when written raw to USB tools such as Rufus, while keeping El Torito floppy-emulation boot.
ITEM Added an AMI-friendlier A20 fallback and disk reset path in the BIOS boot stack.
ITEM Network startup failures now continue offline instead of panicking, improving VirtualBox default-device behavior.
ITEM PS/2 mouse initialization now explicitly enables the aux clock and the default GUI cursor is an arrow instead of a square.
ITEM The idle screensaver counter is slowed to avoid immediate tight-loop activation on fast virtual machines.
ITEM Build, git diff --check, QEMU IMG boot, and QEMU ISO boot were rerun for hotpatch readiness.

SECTION v1.49.0a
ITEM Official promotion of the VM Monitor and Shrine subsystem beta track without feature loss.
ITEM Fixed shrine verify so BOSL .shrine payloads must include valid BOSL magic and supported version before they are accepted.
ITEM Fixed the Shrine/LSS selftest so POST no longer mutates user-visible LSS counters or last-file state.
ITEM Keeps vm status, vm limits, vm selftest, vm clear, and shared step budgets for BOSL, LIL, GASM, Lafillo VM, and OSVM.
ITEM Keeps shrine, lss, and srine status, list, info, verify, run, and test commands plus shrine_guide.lardd.
ITEM Build, LSS host regression, git diff --check, QEMU IMG boot, and QEMU ISO boot were rerun for official-release readiness.
ITEM Release media uses official a-channel versioning with ISO and IMG artifacts.

SECTION v1.48.0b
ITEM Expanded LSS into a visible Shrine subsystem instead of leaving only the hello.shrine sample.
ITEM Added shrine/lss/srine status, list, info, verify, run, and test commands for .shrine wrappers.
ITEM LSS now tracks initialization, runs, failures, verified files, unsupported types, last type, last size, last file, and last error.
ITEM Added shrine_guide.lardd, LardOS control-room links, LUNIT coverage, and POST coverage for hello.shrine plus the LSS wrapper selftest.
ITEM The .shrine wrapper keeps the current in-tree format: LSS\0, one-byte type, and type 0 BOSL payload; type 1 stays reserved.
ITEM Release media uses beta b-channel versioning while the Shrine compatibility surface stabilizes.

SECTION v1.47.0b
ITEM Added VM Monitor for BOSL, LIL, GASM, Lafillo VM, and OSVM.
ITEM Added vm status, vm limits, vm selftest, and vm clear for per-VM runs, failures, budget hits, last steps, max steps, and return code.
ITEM GASM and Lafillo VM now use common step budgets so runaway programs stop instead of hanging the OS surface.
ITEM BOSL JIT now falls back to the budgeted interpreter for branchy programs, keeping loops visible and interruptible.
ITEM Added gasm file.gasm to LSH and vm_guide.lardd to the in-kernel document set.
ITEM POST and LUNIT cover VM Monitor budgets, vm_guide.lardd, and the new vm/gasm command surfaces.
ITEM Release media uses beta b-channel versioning while the VM safety and monitor UI stabilize.

SECTION v1.46.0a
ITEM Official promotion of the LardOS Time beta track without feature loss.
ITEM Keeps LardOS Time ticks from 00000-01-01, five-digit year output, Dangun year, and native lunar display.
ITEM Keeps time, date, lunar, dangun, and lardtime explain shell commands plus SYS_GET_TIME/LIL/BOSL LardOS Time ticks.
ITEM Includes the boot stack, bootinfo, and long-mode stack layout fix for larger in-tree kernels.
ITEM Includes the Lafillo ASM parser forward-progress fix so boot-time language demos do not stall the GUI.
ITEM POST, LUNIT, host lardtime selftest, QEMU IMG boot, and QEMU ISO boot were rerun for official-release readiness.
ITEM Release media uses official a-channel versioning with ISO and IMG artifacts.

SECTION v1.45.0b
ITEM Added LardOS Time: ticks count from 00000-01-01 00:00:00 instead of Unix epoch seconds.
ITEM Added five-digit year output to prevent the visible Y10K bug; years 00000..10000+ print without truncation.
ITEM Added Dangun year view with CE+2333 and the time, date, lunar, and dangun shell commands.
ITEM Added a native lunar calendar estimate anchored to the 02026 lunar new year for in-OS lunar display.
ITEM SYS_GET_TIME, LIL time, and BOSL time now expose LardOS Time ticks while RTC Unix seconds remain internal compatibility input.
ITEM POST and LUNIT now cover the LardOS Time calendar layer and lardtime_guide.lardd.
ITEM Moved the stage2 boot stack, bootinfo block, and long-mode entry stack away from the kernel staging buffer so larger in-tree kernels still boot cleanly.

SECTION v1.44.0a
ITEM Official promotion of the real16 PanicRoom texture, Unicode cursor assignment, and user-editable picture Unicode slot track.
ITEM The default official build now includes cursor set U+E000 plus glyph move/copy/rename/pixel without requiring the beta channel.
ITEM POST, LUNIT, QEMU IMG boot, and QEMU ISO boot were rerun for official-release readiness.
ITEM Release media uses official a-channel versioning with ISO and IMG artifacts.

SECTION v1.43.0b
ITEM Added user-editable assigned Unicode slots: glyph move, glyph copy, glyph rename, and glyph pixel.
ITEM glyph move can reassign a picture character to another U+E000..U+E0FF codepoint while preserving the user's image state.
ITEM Cursor-bound Unicode follows glyph move, so a cursor assigned to U+E000 keeps working after the user moves that slot to another codepoint.
ITEM glyph pixel edits one stored 8x8 picture-glyph cell directly with RRGGBB or AARRGGBB color input and refreshes glyphmap.lardd.
ITEM POST now labels the image-glyph check as user-editable Unicode slot coverage.

SECTION v1.42.0b
ITEM Added Unicode cursor assignment: cursor set U+E000 makes the GUI mouse cursor render from a user-owned picture Unicode slot.
ITEM The cursor renderer reuses the live image-glyph path, so assigned slots keep their realtime hover/click styling when used as a cursor.
ITEM Empty cursor slots safely fall back to the default block cursor until the user loads or demos a picture glyph.
ITEM Added cursor status counters and POST coverage for the Unicode cursor control surface.
ITEM Release media uses beta b-channel versioning while cursor-glyph ergonomics stabilize.

SECTION v1.41.0b
ITEM Beta PanicRoom real-mode texture pass: runtime panic now enters a real16 bridge window before long64 recovery.
ITEM Added a real-mode VGA default texture with an LPR badge, hazard pattern, and REAL16 label drawn from the low-memory trampoline.
ITEM PanicRoom keeps a matching long64 fallback texture so recovery controls stay visible even if the bridge is unavailable.
ITEM Added panicroom texture and CPU mode status counters for real16 PanicRoom texture attempts.
ITEM Release media uses beta b-channel versioning while the new panic recovery visuals stabilize.

SECTION v1.40.0a
ITEM Official promotion of the GUI polish, picture Unicode, clickable live glyph, and rough-edge repair beta track.
ITEM PanicRoom now connects to the real kernel panic path once the runtime is ready: panic and panic_u64 enter the recovery screen before halt.
ITEM The panic recovery screen auto-writes paniccapsule.lardd, shows crashlog.txt, can rebuild the capsule, apply the last rollback snapshot, and drop the first queued task.
ITEM LardKit selftest now verifies PanicRoom enter, capsule generation, and exit state for official-release readiness.
ITEM Release media uses official a-channel versioning with ISO and IMG artifacts.

SECTION v1.39.0b
ITEM Rough-edge repair pass for older features that only barely worked before the image glyph polish.
ITEM Fixed directory browsing so dir X: lists read-only system/LFS files and dir Z: lists every writable RAM file instead of a stale hardcoded subset.
ITEM Made notes add and notes clear keep notes.lardd and the GUI-visible notes.txt in sync.
ITEM Improved LARSView with reload, back, and actions commands plus previous-document status.
ITEM Added POST/LUNIT coverage for the repaired writable directory and command surfaces.

SECTION v1.38.0b
ITEM Made image glyphs clickable in the GUI by recording per-frame hitboxes for rendered PUA picture characters.
ITEM Added realtime glyph rendering with live shimmer, hover outline, and click flash using the GUI tick.
ITEM Added glyph live U+E000 on/off and glyph click U+E000 commands, with live state and click counts exported to glyphmap.lardd.
ITEM Added POST coverage for clickable image glyph hitboxes while keeping the classic text renderer path intact.

SECTION v1.37.0b
ITEM Expanded TempleOS-style picture Unicode into a 256-slot user-owned PUA range, U+E000..U+E0FF.
ITEM Added glyph commands for demo patterns, BMP loading, automatic slot assignment, metadata display, insertion into writable files, and glyphmap.lardd export.
ITEM Added glyph_guide.lardd, writable glyphmap.lardd, LUNIT command coverage, and POST coverage for the image glyph registry.
ITEM The Gallery sample now names U+E000 as sample.bmp, refreshes glyphmap.lardd, and points users to glyph list/auto commands.

SECTION v1.36.0b
ITEM Beta GUI polish pass: refreshed the classic GUI chrome with a warmer multi-accent palette, clearer focus rings, and cleaner input/output frames.
ITEM Improved EXGUI desktop wallpaper, panels, managed window cards, and task/dock surfaces without replacing existing GUI behavior.
ITEM Improved EXEXGUI split layout styling with softer panels, clearer pane labels, workspace markers, and less harsh separator colors.
ITEM Updated the default LGUILIB overlay theme so native GUI library themes start from the new visual direction.

SECTION v1.35.1b
ITEM Beta polish: added exact user-facing command spelling for post baseline as an alias of postbaseline show.
ITEM Updated help and native docs so lardtrace, post baseline, boot replay, cfg profile, and bugreplay draw are visible by the requested names.
ITEM Kept the recovery/audit feature suite in the beta channel while the broad tools continue to stabilize.

SECTION v1.35.0b
ITEM Beta release channel split: LardOS no longer treats every feature release as an official a build by default.
ITEM Added release policy so the shell explains a, b, and p channel use inside the OS.
ITEM Documented that large experimental kernel, GUI, filesystem, or shell bundles should ship as b until promoted.
ITEM Kept p reserved for narrow emergency hotpatches and a reserved for verified official builds.

SECTION v1.34.0a
ITEM Added LardTrace with trace on, trace show, and trace module filters for shell, GUI, OSLink, TaskPrio, network, and package events.
ITEM Added NetWatch, POST baseline reports, BootReplay, LARDD journal, Device Map, CFG profiles, User Law, and LUNIT tests.
ITEM Expanded BugReplay with a draw panel and Magic with dryrun mode.
ITEM Added EXEXGUI workspaces 1/2/3, LTheme preview, LARS app command aliases, and mode guard.
ITEM Added writable trace.lardd, netwatch.lardd, journal.lardd, postbaseline.lardd, bootreplay.lardd, cfgprof.lardd, userlaw.lardd, plus tests.lunit.
ITEM POST now checks the new native recovery, audit, policy, and test files.

SECTION v1.33.0a
ITEM Added BugReplay, a native screen-bug replay log that records BugEye scan frames and writes bugreplay.lardd.
ITEM Added Trust history so permission allow/deny changes are auditable without taking control away from the user.
ITEM Added LPack verify and undo: packages now report structure, hash, installable targets, warnings, and can roll back the last install snapshot.
ITEM Added Panic Capsule, a recovery bundle report that gathers panic, crashlog, BugEye, BugReplay, Trust, TaskPrio, LFSDoctor, and BootMap state into paniccapsule.lardd.
ITEM Added LFSDoctor scan/repair reports for the built-in filesystem and LPST persistence state.
ITEM Added POST/selftest coverage for the new writable report files and recovery-control paths.

SECTION v1.32.1p
ITEM Hotpatch: BugEye now writes every scan to writable bugreport.lardd as a native LARDD report.
ITEM Added priority history, task history, and prio history for tracking who granted priority lev.10 and in what sequence.
ITEM Added POST coverage for bugreport.lardd and TaskPrio lev.10 history.

SECTION v1.32.0a
ITEM Added LardKit, a native C feature suite for BugEye, Rollback, Trust, BootMap, PanicRoom, OldCheck, LTheme, AwakeMonitor, OSChat, LARSView, and LARDD notes.
ITEM Added magic explain so the shell records why Magic executed, refused, or failed a prediction.
ITEM Added assistant mood controls with calm, funny, strict, and silent modes.
ITEM Added writable notes.lardd and POST coverage for the new user-control feature suite.

SECTION v1.31.0a
ITEM Added Lard Buddy, an optional roaming assistant overlay with casual tips and jokes.
ITEM Added buddy on, buddy off, buddy status, buddy joke, and buddy next commands plus assistant/lardbuddy aliases.
ITEM CFGSH can now toggle the assistant with buddy on or buddy off.
ITEM POST now checks the Lard Buddy assistant state machine.

SECTION v1.30.0a
ITEM Added CFGSH, a settings-focused shell that accepts mode-name value commands.
ITEM cfgsh enters a CFG prompt for settings only; cfg and settings run one-shot changes from normal LSH.
ITEM Added numeric setting maps for style, layout, pane, HTTP method, boot profile, and task priority.
ITEM POST now checks the CFGSH grammar map so numbered settings stay covered.

SECTION v1.29.0a
ITEM Awakening mode is now explicitly default-off and controlled through awake on and awake off.
ITEM awake on stores the awakening boot profile for the next boot without changing the current startup path.
ITEM awake off stores the normal boot profile and stops the current Awakening background loader if it is still running.
ITEM The kernel now snapshots the boot-time Awakening choice so runtime profile edits do not accidentally start boot-only loaders.

SECTION v1.28.0a
ITEM Made TaskPrio lev.10 user-grantable to match LardOS full-control values.
ITEM Users can now assign urgent priority with task urgent id, task set id 10, prio id 10, nice 10 command, task default 10, or task boost.
ITEM lev.10 tasks can be lowered, paused, resumed, or dropped by the user; wait-time aging still cannot create lev.10.
ITEM POST TaskPrio selftest now covers user-created lev.10 and demotion back to normal priority.

SECTION v1.27.0a
ITEM Added Awakening mode, a boot profile that shows the GUI/shell surface after essential core init.
ITEM In awakening boot, drivers, LSS/language demo warmup, and networking continue through a quiet background loader.
ITEM Added awake status and awake test commands, plus status/BootProf reporting for the background phase.
ITEM POST now checks the Awakening tracker and bootprof supports bootprof set awakening.

SECTION v1.26.0a
ITEM Added TaskPrio priority lev.10 as an OS-only urgent scheduling level.
ITEM User commands and wait-time aging still stop at priorities 0..9; lev.10 can only be granted by the OS.
ITEM The scheduler now picks an unpaused lev.10 task before all normal task scoring, matching the stop-and-handle-first rule.
ITEM tasktop, status, docs, and POST selftest now cover the reserved lev.10 path.

SECTION v1.25.0a
ITEM Added LGUILIB, a native LardOS GUI library file format stored as .lguilib records.
ITEM Added default.lguilib to the embedded filesystem with NAME, COLOR, WIDGET, and END records.
ITEM GUIOverlay now reads its colors and widget hints from the active LGUILIB theme instead of only hardcoded constants.
ITEM Added lguilib status, show, use, and test commands in LSH, plus POST coverage for the parser and built-in file.

SECTION v1.24.0a
ITEM Added GUIOverlay, a separate chrome layer drawn above the classic GUI.
ITEM Moved title/status text, compact safe tab repainting, button feedback, shadows, and output framing into the overlay path.
ITEM Restored the base GUI hitboxes and fixed controls while keeping the visual improvements as an overlaid layer.
ITEM POST now checks the GUIOverlay layout selftest through the GUI chrome check.

SECTION v1.23.0a
ITEM Improved the classic GUI chrome without replacing the existing GUI.
ITEM Added title/status text, compact safe tab labels, expanding input width, button hover/pressed feedback, and a framed output view.
ITEM POST now checks the polished GUI chrome layout so visual regressions are caught with the boot diagnostics.

SECTION v1.22.0a
ITEM Added EXEXGUI, a sketch-driven split desktop shell.
ITEM EXEXGUI keeps the existing GUI in the left DE/WM pane, mirrors LSH in the top-right terminal pane, and draws an info/status pane below it.
ITEM Added exexgui on, off, status, focus, next, and test commands in LSH.
ITEM POST now checks EXEXGUI layout math so the split GUI regions are covered by boot diagnostics.

SECTION v1.21.0a
ITEM Added EXGUI, an optional extended desktop environment and window-manager layer.
ITEM EXGUI can draw Windows-like, Linux-like, and Mac-like shell chrome without replacing the classic GUI.
ITEM Added exgui on, off, status, style, layout, next, and test commands in LSH.
ITEM POST now checks the EXGUI state machine and the built-in LARS control room links to EXGUI.

SECTION v1.20.0a
ITEM Extended OSLink with a local in-kernel bus for LardOS-internal communication.
ITEM Added oslink bus and oslink emit channel text commands in LSH.
ITEM Local OSLink messages share the existing inbox and are labeled with lightweight channels.
ITEM POST now checks both OSLink packet framing and the local bus path.

SECTION v1.19.0a
ITEM Added ScreenCheck, a structured framebuffer/layout diagnostic module.
ITEM Added screencheck status, retro, and test commands in LSH.
ITEM screencheck retro draws an old boot/storage-style visual scan with colored tiles and a dot-lane visibility check.
ITEM POST now checks ScreenCheck so visible screen regressions are covered by the boot diagnostics.

SECTION v1.18.0a
ITEM Added OSLink EXEC packets for OS-to-OS safe remote command requests.
ITEM Added oslink exec ip command in LSH; receivers queue allowed diagnostics through TaskPrio as remote tasks.
ITEM Remote execution is whitelist-filtered and blocks raw-control commands, pipes, background control, and writes.
ITEM OSLink selftest now covers EXEC packet framing and safe-command filtering.

SECTION v1.17.0a
ITEM Added LardPack, a native LPACK 1 package format parsed and installed by freestanding kernel C.
ITEM Added sample.lpack to the embedded filesystem and lpack info, list, install, and test commands.
ITEM Packages can install files into writable RAM filesystem targets such as notes.txt.
ITEM POST now checks the LardPack parser.

SECTION v1.16.0a
ITEM Added LARS form records with button and input support in the native document renderer.
ITEM Added larsform to list LARS actions and larsact to execute button commands from a LARS document.
ITEM The built-in lardos.lars control room now includes button and input records.
ITEM POST now checks LARS form/action parsing.

SECTION v1.15.0a
ITEM Added CrashLog, a persistent panic and diagnostic event log backed by crashlog.txt.
ITEM panic and panic_u64 now record crash entries and try to save LPST before halting.
ITEM Added crashlog show, clear, test, and selftest commands in LSH.
ITEM status now reports crashlog event count and POST checks that the log is writable.

SECTION v1.14.0a
ITEM Added BootProf, a user-editable boot profile system backed by bootprof.txt.
ITEM Added bootprof status, set, and test commands for normal, safe, netoff, and dev profiles.
ITEM safe forces POST and disables network; netoff skips network; dev raises the default task priority.
ITEM The Doc tab reports network-disabled when a profile intentionally skips networking.
ITEM POST now checks BootProf profile flag behavior.

SECTION v1.13.0a
ITEM Added tasktop, a dashboard-style task manager for the TaskPrio queue.
ITEM Added task up, task down, task pause, and task resume for direct user scheduling control.
ITEM Paused tasks stay visible but are skipped by the background scheduler until resumed.
ITEM Task listings now show runnable and paused counts plus a compact priority bar.

SECTION v1.12.0a
ITEM Added TaskPrio, a user-changeable task priority queue for LSH background work.
ITEM Added task list, task set, task default, task run, task boost, task drop, prio, and nice commands.
ITEM Background commands submitted with & now become numbered tasks with visible priorities.
ITEM The scheduler chooses the highest effective priority and ages waiting tasks so low-priority work is not starved.
ITEM POST now checks the TaskPrio priority queue.

SECTION v1.11.0a
ITEM Added OSLink, a small OS-to-OS communication module over the native UDP stack.
ITEM Added public net_udp_send and net_udp_recv helpers for in-kernel datagram protocols.
ITEM Added oslink status, hello, ping, send, recv, peers, poll, and test commands in LSH.
ITEM OSLink tracks peer nodes, queues incoming messages, and replies to hello, ping, and text packets.
ITEM POST now checks the OSLink packet codec.

SECTION v1.10.0a
ITEM Added ScreenRAM, an optional framebuffer/backbuffer scratch RAM region.
ITEM Added sram and screenram LSH commands for default corner storage, user-selected rectangles, reads, writes, clears, and self-tests.
ITEM ScreenRAM preserves bytes across GUI redraws by restoring the reserved pixel rectangle before blitting.
ITEM POST now checks the ScreenRAM scratch path so visible memory regressions are caught.
ITEM Updated built-in LARS, README, architecture, and LSH docs with the ScreenRAM workflow.

SECTION v1.9.0a
ITEM Added a CPU mode bridge for controlled long64 to real16 and back roundtrips.
ITEM Added cpumode.c and mode_switch.s with a low-memory trampoline at 0x6000.
ITEM Added the LSH mode command with status, probe, and real aliases for explicit bridge tests.
ITEM Added a boot-time M option and POST coverage for CPU mode bridge diagnostics.
ITEM Updated GDT/MMU setup with a 32-bit protected-mode bridge selector and executable low trampoline page.

SECTION v1.8.0a
ITEM Added the magic prefix command for predicted safe command execution.
ITEM magic command [args] corrects near-miss built-in commands and executes the predicted target directly.
ITEM Raw-control commands such as sum, peek, poke, and asm_ are excluded from automatic magic execution.
ITEM Updated LSH help and LARS control-room docs with the magic workflow.

SECTION v1.7.0a
ITEM Added a Doc tab GET/POST method option instead of forcing every HTTP request to GET.
ITEM Added net_http_request and net_https_request so the in-kernel HTTP/TLS path can send POST bodies.
ITEM POST mode reads the Doc address as URL|body, sends Content-Length and application/x-www-form-urlencoded, and keeps GET wrappers for older callers.
ITEM POST redirects are kept conservative: 307/308 preserve POST, while 301/302 leave the original response visible.

SECTION v1.6.0a
ITEM Added an optional Power-On Self-Test prompt during boot.
ITEM Added shared POST diagnostics for CPU mode, heap, native FS docs, LARS/LARDD rendering, LAR archives, DRFL descriptors, PCI options, GUI framebuffer/layout, LPST, LVCS, containers, and LIL feature forms.
ITEM Added the LSH post command as an alias for selftest, using the same POST engine.
ITEM Added GUI framebuffer sampling so POST can catch visible screen/layout failures, not just syntax errors.

SECTION v1.5.0a
ITEM Added C-only mkiso host tooling for bootable El Torito ISO release artifacts.
ITEM Added make release to publish versioned IMG and ISO files under os/release.
ITEM Added run-iso for checking the ISO boot path in QEMU.

SECTION v1.4.0a
ITEM Added LSH lil file execution for native LIL scripts in the in-memory filesystem.
ITEM Added features.lil as an embedded script tour for LIL.
ITEM Extended LIL with assert, when, unless, repeat, stepped for loops, clamp, between, within, pow, gcd, and lcm.
ITEM Updated the host LIL runner to match kernel LIL semantics for printn, emit, defun, for, and new feature forms.

SECTION v1.3.0a
ITEM Added LARS as the native replacement for HTML local documents.
ITEM Added LARDD as the native replacement for Markdown-style project docs.
ITEM Added the kernel lard_doc renderer plus lars, lardd, doc, and release shell commands.
ITEM Switched the Doc tab home file to file://lardos.lars.

SECTION v1.2.0a
ITEM Added full-control LSH surface commands: control, status, peek, poke, write, append, and copy.
ITEM Added SUM-only raw memory controls for user-owned system inspection.
ITEM Removed stale checked-in kernel object files from the build path.

END
